http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Two-arrested-for-robbery-in-Kochi/article14013870.ece

The Kochi city police on Thursday arrested two persons wanted in connection with several robbery cases.The police said the accused, identified as Denson, 28 and Jibin, 27 stole the cell phone of a Kochi native at knife point near Palachuvadu, a couple of days ago. The duo were the members of a robbery gang led by Parunthu Harris, a notorious thief in the city.The police are now on the lookout for Sibi, a native of Thuthiyur, who masterminded the robbery operation. The accused have been remanded to custody.